==Spanish==
===Etymology===
Latin ''[[Castellanus|Castellānus]]''

===Noun===
'''castellano'''

#[[Castilian]].
#[[Castilian Spanish]] as opposed to other varieties of Spanish.
#The [[Spanish]] language generally.

====Synonyms====
*[[español]]

====Usage notes====
In some countries, including Argentina, the language is usually called ''castellano'', even though Argentinian Spanish is quite different than the Castillian variety. In other countries, including Mexico, the language is usually called ''español''.

